en used the methods and themes of their male counterparts to add their voices to the vigorous and prolific debate over the education of women during the eighteenth century. In the texts gathered here, the women discuss the issues they themselves thought most urgent for the equality of women in Italian society specifically and in European culture more broadly. Their thoughts on this important subject reveal how crucial the eighteenth century was in the long history of debates about women in the academy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEducation. 0aWomen. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aknowledge, education, italy, women, gender, italian enlightenment, aretafila savini de rossi, diamante medaglia faini, giuseppa eleonora barbapiccola, maria gaetana agnesi, equality, feminism, nonfiction, history, virtue, career, capacity, intelligence, sexuality, chastity, poetry, philosophy, marriage, masculinity, femininity, domesticity, learning, family, descartes.1 aFaini, Diamante Medaglia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFindlen, Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Margaret L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMessbarger, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRabil, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSavini de' Rossi, Aretafila, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022601054040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226010564423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226010564/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2